Maison Mercedes by @MercedesBenzCanada is a sensorial exhibition of otherworldly luxury right in the heart of Toronto.

The 8,000 sq. ft space features two interactive areas that are inspired by different interpretations of luxury: The Haute Universe, inspired by the Concept Mercedes-Maybach Haute Voiture and The Manufaktur Marketplace, which highlights adventurous luxury with the G-Class, and performance luxury with Mercedes-AMG. 

Each area features its very own retail boutique shops that offer a curated selection of luxurious gifts from brands in Canada and around the world, as well as interactive installations. You can even secure more information and book a test drive from a local Mercedes-Benz dealership.

Now open until December 24th - don’t miss your chance to experience Maison Mercedes for yourself. Maison Mercedes is located at 100 Bloor St. W. in the heart of Toronto’s fashionable Yorkville neighbourhood.

#MaisonMercedes #MercedesBenzCanada #Ad
Wayne Manor 🦇🏰

Drinking whiskey is a magical experience. It's a drink you can savour with close friends or enjoy by yourself in the comfort of your own home. There are quite a number of ways to enjoy whiskey: You can drink it neat or shake or stir it into a modern cocktail. Today, I want to introduce you to @basilhayden, an award-winning Kentucky Bourbon that is light, yet full-bodied. The liquid's refined flavour profile lends plenty of versatility, making it an excellent spirit for cocktails and food pairings. You can enjoy neat, on the rocks, or in a refreshing cocktail such as ‘The Golden Hour’ cocktail in the picture. 🥃

Main Tasting notes:

🔸Aroma: Charred oak and sweet notes of vanilla and caramel with hints of dried fruit.
🔸Taste: Charred oak flavour that is complemented with sweet brown sugar, a touch of black pepper, and dried fruit to round it out.
🔸Finish: A pleasant, lingering charred oak finish with a touch of dried fruit.

📷: @vincentko

 *Must be legal drinking age, please consume responsibly.

#BasilHayden #BuckleandBourbon #KentuckyBourbon #Ad

@BasilHayden was created in Kentucky by Booker Noe in 1992. Booker wanted to craft a more subtle Bourbon to welcome new drinkers, so he used a higher rye mash bill for a more approachable flavour. Today, Basil Hayden remains a symbol of innovation and craftsmanship while embodying an aura of elegance.

Golden Hour is the beautiful time just before sunset when the light warms the earth to a rich golden hue. This cocktail was created to honour the soft, hypnotic warmth of this special moment.

How to make ‘The Golden Hour’ Cocktail:

Ingredients :

🔸1 part Basil Hayden Kentucky Straight Bourbon Whiskey
🔸3/4-part Lillet Blanc
🔸3/4-part Aperol Aperitif
🔸Grapefruit peel

Method:

1. Combine ingredients over ice in a mixing glass.
2. Stir thoroughly.
3. Strain into a chilled cocktail glass over a large ice cube.
4. Garnish with a grapefruit peel.

The Golden Hour is one of my favourite cocktails and it can be easily made at home. Enjoy! 🥃

*Must be legal drinking age, please consume responsibly*

#BasilHayden #BuckleandBourbon #KentuckyBourbon #Ad

Have you visited @bittermelon.to, a new contemporary Asian-Fusion restaurant in Toronto Chinatown? If not, then make sure you add this to your to-do list. 

Bitter Melon is known for their delicious Asian share plates with unconventional touches and inspired cocktails that draw from the Asian pantry. The menu is rooted in East Asia (mainly Chinese, with some Korean and Japanese influence), but South Asian, French and Italian ingredients are married in dishes like beef heart ragu tteokbokki and miso-buttered toast topped with foie gras.

I cannot express how much I am in love with the drinks here. The cocktail list moves from fruity, fresh and floral to bolder and booze-forward, plus a couple of zero-proof options. There is a wide variety of baijius as well as a number of rare Japanese whiskies.

It may be the dead of the Canadian winter, but who says we can’t do something GRAND to celebrate #NationalMargaritaDay on Feb 22 with @grandmarnierofficial? 

I had the pleasure of meeting with and learning from Grand Marnier’s Global Master Blender Patrick Leger who flew in from Cognac, France for the event at @broadviewhotel. The event was filled with educational tastings, immersive cocktail-making, fabulous food with Grand Marnier’s Margarita as the star of the show! 

Here's how you can make your own The Grand Margarita at home:

Ingredients:  
▪️1 oz | Grand Marnier® Cordon Rouge  
▪️1.5 oz | Espolon Tequila  
▪️0.75 oz | freshly squeezed lime juice  
▪️0.5 oz Agave Nectar or Simple Syrup (Optional)
▪️Lime garnish  
--------------------------------------
Process:
1. Fill a wide, shallow dish with 2-3 mm of fine salt. 
2. Cut a lime in half at the width and rub around half of the rim of a margarita glass. 
3. Cut a thin, crosswise slice from one of the lime halves for garnish. 
4. Holding glass upside down, dip wet half delicately into the salt. 
5. Shake Grand Marnier®, Espolon Tequila and lime juice with ice in a cocktail shaker.
6. Strain into glass and apply lime garnish to rim.  

#GrandEncounter #GrandMargarita

Looking for something fun to do this summer? Join the Niagara Whisky Guild and learn more about Forty Creek (@wearefortycreek) and its evolution. Immerse yourself in the history, significance, and future of Forty Creek whisky through the brand’s state of the art 4D museum wall, now available only at the Forty Creek Distillery in Grimsby, ON.

Forty Creek is offering exclusive cocktail classes with award-winning mixologists Nick Kennedy & Aldo Pescatore behind Civil Liberties (@civlibto). For a limited time only this summer, whisky fans can register for courses and earn certifications as you complete three levels of whisky knowledge, gaining hands-on experiences from Forty Creek Master Blender Bill Ashburn, Forty Creek National Brand Ambassador Chris Thompson (@fortycreekchris), and explore all things whisky. From cocktails and world whiskies, to Canadian whisky and a deep dive into Forty Creek, its origins, history and influence on the whisky world, it does not disappoint!

I had such an amazing experience and learned so much from the gents from Civil Liberties and I also got my certificate! 

Make sure to register now while spots are limited! ⬅️

I want to thank the team at Forty Creek for inviting me and letting me be a part of this amazing experience! 

*Must be legal drinking age. Please drink responsibly.

#FortyCreek #FortyCreekWhisky #BelieveInBetter #NiagaraWhisky #Ad
